\nStory continues below advertisement\n\nCorporate executives dominate, but it also includes civil rights advocates, AI\nscientist Fei-Fei Li who leads Stanford University\u2019s AI institute as well as\nMaryland Gov. Wes Moore and Seattle Mayor Bruce Harrell, two public officials\nwho are \u201calready ahead of the curve\u201d in thinking about harnessing AI\u2019s\ncapabilities and mitigating risks, Mayorkas said.\n\nFollow Election 2024\n\nHe said the board will help the Department of Homeland Security stay ahead of\nevolving threats.\n\nAdvertisement\n\nAdvertisement\n\nlive updatespolitics\n\n9:42 PM\n\n#### GOP urges Secret Service to move protesters from park near site of\nMilwaukee convention\n\n9:41 PMMeijer, a Mich. Republican who voted to impeach Trump, drops Senate bid\n\n8:38 PMHow Trump keeps going off-topic outside the courtroom\n\n7:45 PMBiden administration delays menthol cigarette ban again amid political\nconcerns\n\n7:08 PMAnalysis: New evidence that criminal conviction won\u2019t tank Trump\u2019s\ncandidacy\n\nTOP STORIES\n\nPolitics\n\nReporting and analysis from the Hill and the White House\n\nCompeting agendas and cover songs: Inside Trump\u2019s talks with foreign leaders\n\nAnalysis|New evidence that criminal conviction won\u2019t tank Trump\u2019s candidacy\n\nAnalysis|Donald Trump\u2019s casual disparagement of prosecutors as \u2018evil\u2019 and\n\u2018crazy\u2019\n\nback\n\nTry a different topic\n\nSign in or create a free account to save your preferences\n\nAdvertisement\n\nAdvertisement\n\nCompany\n\n* About The Post\n* Newsroom Policies & Standards\n* Diversity & Inclusion\n* Careers\n* Media & Community Relations\n* WP Creative Group\n* Accessibility Statement\n* Sitemap\n\nGet The Post\n\n* Become a Subscriber\n* Gift Subscriptions\n* Mobile & Apps\n* Newsletters & Alerts\n* Washington Post Live\n* Reprints & Permissions\n* Post Store\n* Books & E-Books\n* Print Archives (Subscribers Only)\n* Today\u2019s Paper\n* Public Notices\n